    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-20T06:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-20T06:35:00-05:00" n="406"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5491/11–2045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-20T15:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 20, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 20—11:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>967. Mytel 959 November 19 last paragraph. I am endeavoring obtain Soviet pass
                    for Captain Gagarine Assistant Military Attaché to travel by car to Tabriz and
                    shall also try to send Air Attaché Garver and another officer of my staff by
                    Garver’s plane if weather permits.</p>
                <p>Soviet Military Attaché here has requested that we not apply for passes saying
                    conditions are disturbed and moment inopportune for travel of foreigners in
                    northern Iran. However, he is consulting Soviet headquarters at Qazvin and has
                    promised further word this afternoon. I intend to press matter strongly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
